The paper deals with the problem of deconvolution of signals with sparse spikes, which is a common problem in various fields such as neural recordings, radar and sonar, astronomy, and microscopy. The proposed method involves convex optimization and joint spectral sparsity, which are techniques commonly used in information theory (cs.IT), computer vision (cs.CV), signal processing (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
